
1. login to Azure

1️⃣ Login to Azure:-
____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

*1 login to azure portal-->profile-->Switch directory(Azure Active Directory)-->then pick Directory ID.
    Directory Id:- Issi ko hi tenant kehte hai jiska use hamlog login karne m hota hai.

*2  run this command from cmd:- az login --tenant jahjdhj123hhf (TenantID).
    Verify login hua or nahi:- az account show

*3 Create resource group now:- az group create --name aks20250527 --location centralindia
    NOTE:- aks20250527:- yeah mera resource group ka name hoga.

*4 Now verify ki create resource group bana or nahi.
   1. Command:- az group show --name aks20250527 --output table
   2. Verify from UI:- resource group search kar in search baar and dekho ki aks20250527 is name s koi resource group bana hai or nahi.
      or directly resource group jo banaye ho(aks20250527) usko search baar m search karo.

____________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________

2️⃣ Now Create AKS Cluster:
   Command:- az aks create --resource-group aks20250527 --name akscluster20250527 --node-count 1 --generate-ssh-keys

    BELOW EXPLANATION OF COMMAND:-

    1. az:-	Azure CLI ka base command
    2. aks:-	Azure Kubernetes Service module (AKS se related commands)
    3. create:-	Naya AKS cluster banane ke liye
    4. --resource-group aks20250527:-	Jis resource group me cluster banana hai (yahan: aks20250527)
    5. --name akscluster20250527:-	Cluster ka naam (jo aap rakh rahe ho: akscluster20250527)
    6. --node-count 1:-	Kitne VM nodes hone chahiye cluster me (yahan 1 node)
    7. --generate-ssh-keys:-  SSH ke liye automatic public/private keys generate karega

6. Now,Verify ki cluster bana hai or nahi:-
   Verify Command:- az aks get-credentials --resource-group aks20250527 --name akscluster20250527
   Verify Nodes:- kubectl get nodes

7. Now,Verify ki cluster bana hai or nahi from UI:-
   1. Search → Kubernetes services--> Click on it --> Yahan aapko aapka cluster dikhega: akscluster20250527
   2. Now search in left search bar as 'Node Pools' --> yaha p apko apke node ka sara status dikh jayega.

