1. GitHub Actions OIDC Integration with Azure(Open Id Connect):-

   1 Purpose:- OpenID(OIDC) isley connect karte hain taki Github ko Azure me secure tarike se login karne diya jaye.
               ** Bina username and password ya secrets ke - bas ek trusted identity k through.

1. Go to the Azure Portal Home: https://portal.azure.com
2. In the Search bar at the top, type: App registrations
3. Click on the result that says App registrations under Services
4. Now you’re on the App registrations page → Click on "+ New registration"
5. Now you’re on the “Register an application” screen:-
   *1 Fill in the following:
      Name:- aks-gh-actions-app
   *2 Supported account types:
      Select::- Accounts in this organizational directory only (Default Directory only - Single tenant)
   *3 Redirect URI (optional):- Leave it blank for now. (We don’t need it for GitHub Actions OIDC)

✅ Step 3: Create a Client Secret:-
   ** Now we’ll generate a client secret for this app.

   *1 In the left-hand menu under your app, click on "Certificates & secrets".
   *2 Under the "Client secrets" section, click “+ New client secret”.
   *3 Fill:-
      *1 Description:-  You can write gh-actions-secret
      *2 Expires: Choose 6 months or 12 months as per your policy.
      *3 Click “Add”
   *4 ⚠️ Copy the value of the secret immediately. You won’t see it again later. Keep it safe for now.

      6bc418ba-c0fd-401b-8374-ffbfc212af0a

✅ Step 4: Get Required Azure Credentials for GitHub Secret

   ** Now we’ll collect all the credentials that GitHub needs to log in to Azure via the workflow.
      You need to note down the following 4 details:

      1. Subscription ID  2. Tenant ID  3. Client ID (Application ID)  4. Client Secret (from previous step)

   *1 Subscription ID:-
      *1 From Azure Portal homepage --> Search and go to "Subscriptions"  -->  Open your active subscription  --> Copy the Subscription ID

61de3f12-73d3-4f86-ae76-cd7e94e6de86


   *2 Tenant ID:-
      *1 Azure portal home pe jao --> Search karo: "Azure Active Directory" --> Open karo → Overview tab → Wahan Tenant ID clearly dikh jayega ✅
         13318b29-4236-41c7-a64b-ae1cc92c138f

   *3 Client ID (Application ID):-
      *1 Search for App Registration → All Applications tab --> look for App registration name which you created in first step --> copy client ID

   *4 You should have copied it when you created it in Step 3

   *4 Client Secret (from previous step):-
      *1 You should copy from step 3.if forget follow step no 3 once again and generate it.


